# CIAM Touch RFID Button v3

IoT device firmware for an ESP8266-based (WeMos D1 mini) RFID and capacitive touch button reader that publishes events to a Flatbox cloud platform via MQTT.

**Firmware Version:** V5.00 | **Hardware Version:** V3.00

## Features

- RFID card reading via SoftwareSerial (9600 baud)
- Capacitive touch button detection
- MQTT event publishing to Flatbox IoT platform (JSON format)
- WiFi configuration portal via WiFiManager (on-demand)
- OTA (Over-the-Air) firmware updates
- NTP time synchronization
- RGB LED and piezo buzzer feedback
- Device health monitoring (WiFi RSSI, message counters, battery voltage)
- MQTT connect safeguard: 4 retries then WiFiManager fallback for config correction
- Automatic restart on persistent MQTT failures (150 threshold)
- LittleFS-based persistent configuration storage

## Hardware

| Pin | Function         | Component             |
|-----|------------------|-----------------------|
| D0  | Touch Button     | Capacitive Touch Pad  |
| D2  | RFID TX          | RFID Reader (SSerial) |
| D3  | RFID RX          | RFID Reader (SSerial) |
| D4  | RGB Purple       | RGB LED               |
| D5  | Buzzer           | Piezo Buzzer          |
| D6  | RGB Blue/White   | RGB LED               |
| D7  | RGB Green/White  | RGB LED               |
| D8  | RGB Red/White    | RGB LED               |
| A0  | Battery Voltage  | Battery Monitor       |

## Project Structure

```
в”ңв”Җв”Җ include/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ Settings.h              # Device config, MQTT topics, credentials, thresholds
в”ңв”Җв”Җ lib/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ Buzzer/src/             # BTN_Bzzr - piezo buzzer control
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ Flatbox_publish/src/    # flatbox - MQTT JSON payload formatting
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ NTP_Client/src/         # NTPClient - UDP time synchronization
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ RGB/src/                # BlinkRGB / BlinkColor - LED control
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ TimeESP/src/            # TimeLibEsp - date/time management
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ TouchBtn/src/           # TouchPadButton - capacitive input
в”ңв”Җв”Җ src/
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.cpp                # Application entry point and FSM logic
в””в”Җв”Җ platformio.ini              # Build configuration (espressif8266, d1_mini)
```

## Finite State Machine

The firmware runs a priority-based finite state machine with 7 states. Event priority is **card > button > timers** -- higher-priority events preempt lower-priority checks within the IDLE state.

