### State Transition Summary

| From State | To State | Trigger |
| --- | --- | --- |
| IDLE | TRANSMIT_CARD_DATA | RFID card detected by `readTag()` (non-duplicate) |
| IDLE | TRANSMIT_BOTON_DATA | Button press detected by `readBtn()` |
| IDLE | UPDATE | 30-minute periodic timer expires |
| IDLE | UPDATE_TIME | 60-minute NTP resync timer expires |
| IDLE | (restart) | Failed MQTT messages exceed threshold (150) |
| TRANSMIT_BOTON_DATA | IDLE | After publishing button event |
| TRANSMIT_CARD_DATA | IDLE | After publishing card event |
| UPDATE | TRANSMIT_DEVICE_UPDATE | Always (msg carries "on" or "LOWiFi") |
| TRANSMIT_DEVICE_UPDATE | IDLE | After publishing device data |
| UPDATE_TIME | IDLE | After NTP sync (up to 5 retries) |
| RDY_TO_UPDATE_OTA | RDY_TO_UPDATE_OTA | Loops waiting for OTA upload |
| (any unknown) | IDLE | Default handler resets to IDLE |

## MQTT Communication

- **Broker:** Configurable (default: `adnode.flatbox.io:1883`)
- **Auth:** Username + token-based
- **Publish topic:** `iot-2/evt/status/fmt/json`
- **Subscribe topics:** Device management, response, update, and reboot channels

### Event Payload Example

```json
{
  "d": {
    "botondata": {
      "ChipID": "device_id",
      "IDEventoBoton": "CIAM-1",
      "Tstamp": "2026-03-04T12:00:00"
    }
  }
}
```

## Configuration (LittleFS)

Stored as `/config.json` on the device flash:

| Parameter             | Default              |
|-----------------------|----------------------|
| MQTT_Server           | adnode.flatbox.io    |
| MQTT_Port             | 1883                 |
| MQTT_User             | demo                 |
| MQTT_Password         | demo                 |
| NTPClient_SERVER      | time-a-g.nist.gov    |
| NTPClient_interval    | 60000 (ms)           |

## Startup Behavior

1. Load config from LittleFS
2. **First 2-second window:** Hold button to enter WiFi configuration portal
3. **Second 2-second window:** Hold button to enter OTA update mode
4. Otherwise: Auto-connect WiFi, sync NTP, connect MQTT (4 retries, falls back to WiFiManager on failure), enter IDLE state

## Build

Requires [PlatformIO](https://platformio.org/).

```bash
# Build
pio run

# Upload via serial
pio run --target upload

# Monitor serial output
pio device monitor -b 115200
```

## Dependencies

- ESP8266WiFi / WiFiUdp
- WiFiManager v2.x
- PubSubClient v2.8 (MQTT)
- ArduinoJson v7
- ArduinoOTA
- ESP8266WebServer / ESP8266mDNS / DNSServer
- LittleFS (FS)

## Known Limitations

- NTP synchronization can be slow on startup (mitigated with 5-retry loop)
- Maximum MQTT payload buffer: 300 bytes
- Credentials are stored in source code (Settings.h)

## Changelog

### v5.00 - Pre-release Hardening

Storage migration:

- Migrated from SPIFFS to LittleFS (SPIFFS deprecated on ESP8266)

Library updates:

- ArduinoJson v5.13 -> v7 (all 8 call sites migrated to new API)
- WiFiManager v0.16 -> v2.x
- Removed incompatible SoftwareSerialEsp32 dependency (ESP8266 provides SoftwareSerial natively)
- Fixed SoftwareSerial constructor to 3-arg form (v8.x API)

FSM fixes (round 1):

- Added `default:` case to switch -- resets unknown states to IDLE with serial warning
- Fixed `checkalarms()` -- `BeepSignalWarning` only resets when RSSI is above threshold
- `STATE_UPDATE` no longer overwrites `STATE_TRANSMIT_ALARM_UPDATE` set by `updateDeviceInfo()`
- Added MQTT reconnect checks before publish in `TRANSMIT_BOTON_DATA` and `TRANSMIT_CARD_DATA`
- Added early-exit guards in IDLE to enforce event priority (card > button > timers)

FSM fixes (round 2):

- `MQTTreconnect()` capped at 3 retries per call (was infinite loop, could block 30+ seconds)
- `NormalReset()` now checks MQTT connection and calls `CheckTime()` before publishing
- `readTag()` rejects duplicate consecutive card reads early (before LED/buzzer/state change)
- RFID read delay reduced from 10ms to 2ms per byte (120ms -> 24ms total blocking)
- Merged `STATE_TRANSMIT_ALARM_UPDATE` into `STATE_TRANSMIT_DEVICE_UPDATE` (identical logic, `msg` field carries the distinction)
- Unified RSSI alarm threshold to `RSSI_LOW_THRESHOLD` constant in Settings.h (was -85 in `checkalarms()` vs -75 in `updateDeviceInfo()`)
- `failed` counter now halves on success instead of zeroing (prevents masking persistent degradation)

Library bug fixes:

- **BUG FIX:** `BlinkColor` constructor stored `pin1` into `_pin2` (third LED channel never worked)
- **BUG FIX:** `TouchPadButton._prev_Button_State` was uninitialized (could miss first button press)
- **BUG FIX:** `Flatbox_Publish.Administracion_Dispositivo` had duplicate JSON field (`publicados` and `enviados` both mapped to same value). Added `sent` parameter to differentiate published vs sent counters.
- Consolidated 3 `flatbox` instances into 1 (saved 1,828 bytes RAM -- 43.7% -> 41.5%)
- Commented out unused methods across all libraries to reduce flash/RAM footprint:
  - Buzzer: `This_Bzzr_State()`, `Change_Bzzr_State()`
  - RGB: `BlinkRGB::Change_RGB_State()`
  - NTP_Client: `getHours()`, `getMinutes()`, `getSeconds()`, `getFormattedTime()`, 3 unused constructors
  - TimeESP: `hourFormat12()`, `isAM()`, `isPM()`, `adjustTime()`, `setSyncInterval()`, entire `DateStrings.cpp`
- Fixed broken macros in TimeLibEsp.h (`minutesToTime_t`, `hoursToTime_t`, etc. had double-paren syntax)

TimeESP library rewrite:

- Rewrote lib/TimeESP from 4 files (553 lines) down to 2 files (155 lines)
- Deleted `TimeEsp.h` (redirect header), `DateStrings.cpp` (fully commented out)
- Deleted legacy files: `examples/` directory (11 sketches), `Readme.txt`, `keywords.txt`, `library.json`, `library.properties`
- Kept identical API surface -- zero changes to main.cpp required
- New `TimeLibEsp.h`: types, constants, and only the function declarations used by the project
- New `TimeESP.cpp`: clean implementations with no commented-out blocks

MQTT connection safeguard:

- `mqttConnect()` reduced from 30 retries + blind `ESP.restart()` to 4 retries + WiFiManager fallback
- On 4 failed attempts, opens on-demand WiFiManager config portal so user can correct MQTT server/port/credentials
- After saving new config, device restarts with corrected settings
- Prints PubSubClient return code (`rc=`) on each failure to aid diagnosis

Code quality:

- Added include guard to Settings.h
- Added `build_flags = -DMQTT_MAX_PACKET_SIZE=512` for PubSubClient
- Pinned library versions in platformio.ini
